There was a person who went back to the hospice.

18
00:02:20.430 --> 00:02:23.530
Her wife was a guardian.

19
00:02:24.630 --> 00:02:31.250
She was determined to help her husband so that he
could be comfortable with the patient at home.

20
00:02:34.850 --> 00:02:38.790
The patient was in a very difficult situation as the
body was progressing quickly.

21
00:02:38.790 --> 00:02:43.450
In many situations, the guardian was very tired.

22
00:02:44.250 --> 00:02:47.190
Then, the guardian was very tired.

23
00:02:48.390 --> 00:02:50.410
And her children were living abroad.

24
00:02:52.570 --> 00:02:56.230
The guardian needed a lot of help.

25
00:02:58.130 --> 00:03:04.250
Whenever we needed help, we called her or found her
and helped her.

26
00:03:04.250 --> 00:03:08.210
There was a limit to that.

27
00:03:08.430 --> 00:03:16.790
The guardian was very tired. After discussing with
the guardian, we moved the patient to the assisted living room.

28
00:03:19.210 --> 00:03:22.470
The guardian was able to accept the patient
comfortably until he was helped there.

29
00:03:25.910 --> 00:03:29.210
To be honest, the guardian needed a lot of help.

30
00:03:29.210 --> 00:03:31.510
To be honest, it was a difficult case for me.

31
00:03:31.810 --> 00:03:36.170
The guardian told me at the end of the story.

32
00:03:36.810 --> 00:03:40.430
After listening to the story, everything that was
hard for me disappeared.

33
00:03:41.670 --> 00:03:47.170
The guardian told me that he was with me from the
beginning to the end.

34
00:03:48.050 --> 00:03:49.150
He said thank you so much.

35
00:03:49.150 --> 00:03:59.390
After listening to the story, everything was
forgotten.

36
00:04:07.020 --> 00:04:13.960
I was very nervous. After listening to the story, I
was very nervous.

37
